		<exercise>
			<statement>
				<p>
					Looking at the “number of bonds” column for carbon, what do you notice that is special about carbon compared to the other neutral (ie. zero charge) elements in this chart? How does this make carbon more versatile than any other element?
				</p>
			</statement>
			<answer>
				<p>
					Carbon can make 4 bonds, which is more than any other element in the table.  This allows carbons to form a larger variety of structures than other elements
				</p>
			</answer>
